= Sinatra, Ramaze and Rails on Tokyo

* Ruby (1.8, 1.9)
* Tokyo Cabinet
* Tokyo Tyrant (optional)
* Tokyo Dystopia (optional) TODO


== Framework

* manveru-ramaze (2009.06.04)
* sinatra (0.9.2)
* rails (2.3.2)


== Clients

Each demo has it's folder name based on the client used:

rufus:: rufus-tokyo http://github.com/jmettraux/rufus-tokyo
cab:: cabinet http://tokyocabinet.sourceforge.net/rubypkg
tyr:: tyrant http://tokyocabinet.sourceforge.net/tyrantrubypkg

Using DataMapper:

dm-tokyo-adapter::  http://github.com/shanna/dm-tokyo-adapter


== Gems

* dm-core (0.10+)
* haml
* rspec
* cucumber


== Tokyo Cabinet

You can choose between Cabinet or Tyrant on the project`s config files.
Tyrant as default on port 1978 (ttserver something.tct)
Don't forget the .tct


